[[Category:Physics]]

A set of cards is called a '''pack'''. A normal pack has 52 cards in it. These are split into four types, known as '''suits''', called '''hearts''', '''clubs''', '''diamonds''' and '''spades'''. There are numbers on the cards, and there is one card of each number in each suit. Some of the cards have a letter rather than a number on them: ones have the letter '''A''' on them, and are known as '''aces''', elevens, twelves and thirteens are known as '''Jacks''', '''Queens''' and '''Kings''', and have the letters J, Q, and K on them. Some games use special cards called '''jokers'''. If jokers are used, there are usually 54 cards in the pack.
==The pack== The following cards are in a pack:
