Direct Objects in Japanese are usually located at the beginning of a sentence to identify at first what is needed to be done. Tenses do not effect Direct objects.
{{Stub}}
[[Category:Japanese|Japanese/Word Functions]]

Indirect objects are located in the middle of the section to identify which object is partially in respect to where, who, what, why, or how an object is. Tenses effect indirect objects.

{{stub}}
[[Category:Japanese|Japanese/Word Functions]]

